summary: TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 2017 NISSAN MURANO. THE CONTACT STATED THAT WHILE DRIVING APPROXIMATELY 65 MPH, THE GLASS MOON ROOF EXPLODED WITHOUT IMPACT. THE MOON ROOF WAS CLOSED WHEN THE FAILURE OCCURRED. THE VEHICLE WAS NOT TAKEN TO BE INSPECTED OR DIAGNOSED. THE VEHICLE WAS TAKEN TO THE LOCAL GLASS REPAIR FACILITY TO BE REPAIRED. THE MANUFACTURER WAS NOTIFIED OF THE FAILURE. THE LOCAL DEALER WAS NOT CONTACTED. THE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS 26,000.
